This paper deals with deep neural networks for semantic image segmentation, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel loss max-pooling concept for handling imbalanced training data distributions, which is a technique that can be applied to improve the performance of deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
